OL,3,CWatchdog opens new probe into Thames
OL,4,CWater over delays to environmental work
OL,6,FThames is currently the only firm
OL,7,Fregulated by Ofwat to be facing a
OL,8,Fprobe into its environmental
OL,9,Fprotection programmes.
OL,11,FMeanwhile, the parent company of the
OL,12,Fembattled utilities firm is set to run
OL,13,Fout of money by late March and risks
OL,14,Fentering special administration if it
OL,15,Fdoes not get court approval for a
OL,16,Frestructuring plan.
OL,18,FIt is in about #16 billion of debt and
OL,19,Fneeds #3.3 billion over the next five
OL,20,Fyears to keep running.
